At resonance, the frequency $ f $ is given by:

$$
f = \frac{1}{2\pi\sqrt{LC}}
$$

Substitute the given values:  
- $ L = 10 \, \text{mH} = 10 \times 10^{-3} \, \text{H} $  
- $ C = 1 \, \mu\text{F} = 1 \times 10^{-6} \, \text{F} $

Now,  
$$
f = \frac{1}{2\pi \sqrt{10 \times 10^{-3} \cdot 1 \times 10^{-6}}}  
= \frac{1}{2\pi \sqrt{10^{-8}}}  
$$
$$
= \frac{1}{2\pi \cdot 10^{-4}}  
\approx \frac{1}{6.28 \times 10^{-4}}  
\approx 1591 \, \text{Hz} = 1.59 \, \text{kHz}
$$

So, the resonance frequency is:  
$$
\boxed{1.59 \, \text{kHz}}
$$

