Given:
- Damping equation:  
  $$
  Q = Q_0 e^{-\frac{R t}{2L}}
  $$

We are told:
- $ Q = 0.5 Q_0 $
- $ R = 1.5 \, \Omega $
- $ L = 12 \, \text{mH} = 12 \times 10^{-3} \, \text{H} $
- $ \ln(2) = 0.693 $

Set up the equation:  
$$
0.5 Q_0 = Q_0 e^{-\frac{R t}{2L}}
$$

Divide both sides by $ Q_0 $:  
$$
0.5 = e^{-\frac{R t}{2L}}
$$

Take natural logarithm on both sides:  
$$
\ln(0.5) = -\frac{R t}{2L}  
\Rightarrow -0.693 = -\frac{1.5 \cdot t}{2 \cdot 12 \times 10^{-3}}
$$

Simplify:  
$$
0.693 = \frac{1.5 \cdot t}{0.024}
\Rightarrow t = \frac{0.693 \cdot 0.024}{1.5}
= \frac{0.016632}{1.5}
\approx 0.01109 \, \text{s} = 11.09 \, \text{ms}
$$
